VALUES
(40, 3, 12, 23, 41, 16, 16, 'fan', 'Purging and Scattering Imagery', 'This connection highlights the imagery of fanning and purging in both passages. Matthew speaks of gathering wheat and burning chaff, while Isaiah describes fanning and scattering, emphasizing the separation of the righteous from the wicked.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 12, 24, 51, 2, 2, 'fan is in his hand', 'Fanning and Purging Imagery', 'This connection highlights the imagery of fanning used in both passages, where the act of separating wheat from chaff in Matthew parallels the fanners sent to Babylon in Jeremiah. Both verses emphasize the theme of purification and judgment.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 12, 19, 1, 4, 4, 'the chaff', 'Chaff and Judgment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the fate of the chaff, illustrating its worthlessness and ultimate destruction. Matthew describes the burning of chaff, while Psalms compares the ungodly to chaff driven away by the wind.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 12, 40, 13, 41, 41, 'gather his wheat into the garner', 'Judgment and Separation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of the righteous and the removal of the wicked. The imagery of purging and gathering in Matthew 3:12 parallels the gathering of offenders in Matthew 13:41.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 13, 43, 1, 32, 34, 'to be baptized of him', 'Baptism and Divine Revelation', 'This connection highlights the significance of Jesus'' baptism by John, which is a pivotal moment where the Spirit descends upon Him, affirming His identity as the Son of God. Both passages emphasize the act of baptism as a divine revelation of Jesus'' mission and identity.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 13, 40, 2, 22, 22, 'cometh Jesus from Galilee', 'Jesus'' Journey from Galilee', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' movement from Galilee to Judea, as seen in both passages. In Matthew 2:22, Jesus is associated with Galilee, while Matthew 3:13 shows Him coming from Galilee to be baptized.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 13, 41, 1, 9, 11, 'baptized of him', 'Baptism of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' baptism by John in the Jordan. They describe the event as a significant moment in Jesus'' ministry, highlighting the divine affirmation of his identity.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 13, 42, 3, 21, 22, 'to be baptized of him', 'Baptism of Jesus Connection', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus being baptized, highlighting a significant moment in his ministry. The connection is further reinforced by the mention of divine approval in Luke, which follows the act of baptism in Matthew.', 'parallel', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 14, 43, 3, 3, 7, NULL, 'Baptism and Spiritual Birth', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation through baptism and spiritual rebirth. Both passages emphasize the necessity of a new beginning, whether through John''s baptism or being ''born again'' as Jesus describes.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 14, 43, 13, 6, 8, 'I have need to be baptized of thee', 'Baptism and Cleansing', 'This connection highlights the theme of purification and the necessity of accepting a form of cleansing. In both passages, there is a reluctance to accept the act of being cleansed, whether through baptism or foot washing.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 14, 44, 1, 5, 8, NULL, 'Baptism and Empowerment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of baptism, with John recognizing the need for a greater baptism than his own. Matthew highlights John''s water baptism, while Acts contrasts it with the baptism of the Holy Ghost, indicating a progression in spiritual empowerment.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 14, 42, 1, 43, 43, NULL, 'Recognition of Authority', 'Both passages emphasize a sense of unworthiness in the presence of a greater authority. John feels he should be baptized by Jesus, while Elizabeth questions her worthiness to receive Mary, the mother of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 14, 45, 3, 23, 23, 'I have need to be baptized of thee', 'Baptism and Human Sinfulness', 'This connection highlights the recognition of human sinfulness. John''s reluctance to baptize Jesus reflects the understanding that all have sinned, as stated in Romans.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 14, 48, 3, 22, 22, 'I have need to be baptized of thee', 'Baptism and Faith Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of baptism and its relationship to faith. John recognizes the need for a higher authority in baptism, paralleling the idea in Galatians that faith in Jesus Christ is essential for salvation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 14, 48, 4, 6, 6, NULL, 'Baptism and Sonship Connection', 'This connection highlights the transition from John''s baptism to the spiritual adoption of believers as sons of God. Both passages emphasize the importance of divine initiation in the relationship between God and humanity.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 15, 43, 4, 34, 34, 'fulfil all righteousness', 'Connection of Righteousness and Will', 'This connection highlights the theme of fulfilling divine purpose. Both passages emphasize the importance of doing God''s will and completing the work assigned to Jesus.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 15, 23, 42, 21, 21, 'fulfil all righteousness', 'Righteousness and Fulfillment', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteousness in both passages. Matthew emphasizes fulfilling all righteousness, while Isaiah speaks of the Lord being pleased for his righteousness' sake.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 15, 43, 15, 10, 10, 'fulfil all righteousness', 'Righteousness and Commandments', 'This connection highlights the theme of fulfilling divine expectations. Both passages emphasize the importance of obedience to commandments as a means of abiding in love and righteousness.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 15, 19, 40, 7, 8, 'fulfil all righteousness', 'Fulfillment of Righteousness and Will', 'This connection highlights the theme of fulfilling God''s will. Both passages emphasize the importance of obedience to God''s law and the desire to do His will.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 15, 42, 1, 6, 6, 'fulfil all righteousness', 'Righteousness and Blamelessness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteousness in both passages. Matthew emphasizes fulfilling all righteousness, while Luke describes individuals who are blameless in their observance of God''s commandments.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 15, 50, 2, 7, 8, 'fulfil all righteousness', 'Obedience and Humility in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience in both passages. In Matthew 3:15, Jesus emphasizes fulfilling righteousness, while Philippians 2:8 speaks of His obedience unto death, showcasing His humility and commitment to God''s will.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 15, 60, 2, 21, 24, 'fulfil all righteousness', 'Connection of Righteousness and Suffering', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of fulfilling righteousness through suffering. In Matthew, Jesus speaks of fulfilling all righteousness, while 1 Peter highlights Christ''s suffering as an example for believers to follow in living unto righteousness.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 16, 23, 11, 2, 2, 'the Spirit of God descending like a dove', 'Connection of the Spirit''s Presence', 'This connection highlights the descent of the Spirit in Matthew and the Spirit resting upon the figure in Isaiah. Both passages emphasize the role of the Spirit of God in empowering Jesus and the anticipated Messiah.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 16, 41, 1, 10, 10, NULL, 'Baptism and Spirit''s Descent', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus coming up out of the water and the Spirit descending like a dove. This connection highlights the significance of the baptism event in both accounts.', 'parallel', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 16, 42, 3, 21, 22, 'the heavens were opened unto him', 'Baptism and Holy Spirit Connection', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' baptism and the descent of the Spirit. They describe the heavens opening and the Spirit of God appearing like a dove, highlighting a significant moment in Jesus'' ministry.', 'parallel', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 16, 23, 42, 1, 1, 'the Spirit of God descending', 'Connection of Spirit and Servanthood', 'This connection highlights the descent of the Spirit of God upon Jesus in Matthew, paralleling Isaiah''s mention of God''s Spirit being put upon His servant. Both passages emphasize the divine endorsement and empowerment of Jesus as the chosen servant.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 16, 43, 1, 31, 34, NULL, 'Connection of the Spirit''s Descent', 'Both passages emphasize the Spirit descending like a dove, signifying Jesus'' divine anointing. This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus as the Son of God through the manifestation of the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 16, 44, 7, 56, 56, 'the heavens were opened', 'Heavens Opened Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of the heavens being opened in both passages. In Matthew, the heavens open at Jesus'' baptism, while in Acts, they open for Stephen''s vision of the Son of Man.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 3, 16, 26, 1, 1, 1, 'the heavens were opened', 'Heavens Opened Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the opening of the heavens, indicating a divine revelation. In Matthew, this occurs during Jesus'' baptism, while in Ezekiel, it precedes a vision of God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
